<TEXT>
TITLE challengers Northamptonshire beat Nottinghamshire by an innings
and 97 runs to keep in the hunt in the hottest Britannic Assurance
Championship race for years.
All eyes now turn to Uxbridge, where Northants today begin their
showdown with leaders Middlesex, who beat Yorkshire by an innings.
Champions Warwickshire, in the middle of a top three separated by just
11 points, had a 10-wicket victory over Worcestershire.
Northants resumed on 709-7 -- already their highest total and the
biggest by any county this season -- and declared at 781-7. Notts began
their second innings 254 runs adrift with 91 overs remaining and were
dismissed for 157 with just 17 balls left.
