<TEXT>
ORGANISERS of this year's DairyScot event will be increasing
facilities at The Royal Highland Centre at Ingliston by erecting a 1000
sq m marquee as an extension to the exhibition hall. Among the
attractions will be a ''beef from the dairy herd'' demonstration.
Management committee chairman Alex Brown said: ''All the available
trade stand area has been taken up, ensuring a busy day for visitors to
Ingliston on November 29. Our belief that Scotland could justify its own
specialist dairy event has been vindicated.''
