<HEADLINE>Crematorium confounds critics</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650347</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Highlands' first crematorium is doing a brisk trade despite the
predictions of hard-line churchmen who said there would be no demand. In
its first month, the #1.4m complex at Kilvean, outside Inverness, has
exceeded its break-even figure by 10%.
The new facility, built by Inverness District Council after 10 years
of opposition, is handling funerals from as far away as Wick, in the far
north, and Mallaig on the west coast.
</TEXT>
