<HEADLINE>Turkish blasts leave two dead</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650368</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ISTANBUL: Police found three bombs in the car park of a shopping
centre after a series of blasts killed two people and injured about 40
in the Turkish city of Istanbul. The bombs were the sixth and seventh
planted in the city in the past 18 hours.
The dead and about 30 people were injured by two bombs which exploded
in rubbish bins on a pedestrian walkway. Other targets were the chill
cabinet of a restaurant in a tourist district, the offices of a
political party, and a military school. An Islamic group which has
carried out previous attacks claimed responsibility for one blast.
</TEXT>
