<HEADLINE>Bus 'sins' move</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650381</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NICOSIA: Tehran's mini-buses, following in the path of city buses,
will soon have separate sections for women and men in order to avoid
millions of ''sins''. Every day 370,000 women travel by mini-bus and
''if 10 men brush against them intentionally or by mistake, 3.7 million
accountable sins are committed every day'', said Muhammad Ali Tarfa,
head of the public transport authority.
</TEXT>
