<DOCNO>GH950829-000055</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950829-000055</DOCID>
<DATE>950829</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Behaviour incentive</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>31</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650386</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BONUS payments for the Qualifying and Scottish cups will be dependent
on good behaviour, it was decided yesterday.
The winner of both the north and south sections of the Qualifying Cup
will collect #5000. In the Scottish Cup itself the winner will pick up
#37,500 and the beaten finalist #18,750. The eight clubs who are knocked
out in the first round will get #1250 each.
But a caution will cost 10% and an ordering off 20% from the match fee
up to and including the semi-finals. In the final, a caution will cost
#1875 and an ordering off #3750.
Fines will help fund the SFA's Fair Play campaign.
* CHALLENGE Cup. Second-round draw:
Albion Rovers v Brechin; Alloa v Stirling Albion; Dunfermline v
Forfar; Dundee United v Hamilton; Stenhousemuir v Montrose; Livingston v
St Mirren; Dundee v Cowdenbeath; Clydebank v St Johnstone.
Ties to be played on September 12 or 13.
</TEXT>
