<DOCID>GH950829-000057</DOCID>
<DATE>950829</DATE>
<HEADLINE>No Headline Present</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650388</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Education Secretary Gillian Shephard yesterday promised an inquiry
into claims that universities were admitting students without A-levels.
She was commenting on reports that ''hundreds'' of students who have
failed A-level students were getting places on foundation-year courses
at new universities -- former polytechnics -- before going on to study
for degrees.
</TEXT>
