<HEADLINE>Analyst predicts improved credit</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>25</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650396</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WITH the fag end of the month to be completed following the bank
holiday weekend when the markets are closed, it will be Friday before
there are any official economic statistics.
Retail sales perked up in July, and so City analysts are looking for a
strong set of credit figures. James Capel expects net credit to pick up
from June's #591m to around #600m.
With European trade data being compiled from VAT returns, global trade
figures continue to lag behind other statistics. Friday's figures are
for June, when, it is thought, the visible trade gap will have widened
by around #300m to about #1200m.
</TEXT>
