<DOCNO>GH950829-000071</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950829-000071</DOCID>
<DATE>950829</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Graduate gloom</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>24</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650402</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MANY British companies are pessimistic about the next generation of
school-leavers and graduates, according to a new survey today.
A shortage of good workers was quoted as the biggest barrier to future
business success in the poll of 200 medium-sized companies in Britain.
The Mori survey also found that firms are failing to invest in
training and devloping staff.
</TEXT>
