<HEADLINE>Not offended</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>976650436</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Herald is noted for its unbiased view so it can surely be no great
shock to James Faulds that there are things in the paper's content with
which he disagrees (August 26). I for one was not offended by the
inclusion of a leaflet on Transcendental Meditation.
As far as I know, Christianity and TM are not mutually exclusive
but even if I am wrong I am sure the vast majority of readers are
sufficiently broad-minded and intelligent neither to take exception to,
nor be unduly swayed by, the little brochure.
W J O'Hagan,
5 Farm Terrace,
Burnbank, Hamilton.
</TEXT>
