<HEADLINE>What is the point of military prisons?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>976650446</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I AM at a loss to understand why we need military prisons (August 25).
Surely if one is guilty of a criminal offence meriting a prison
sentence, he/she can be dismissed from the Services and prosecuted in
civil life in a civil court?
We do not have prisons dedicated to convicted teachers, lawyers,
doctors, midwives, nurses, shop assistants, unemployed people, business
people, or politicans. Why for soldiers?
Alan R Wilson,
4 Corsebar Crescent,
Paisley.
</TEXT>
