<DATE>950829</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Debate call over sale</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976650463</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SHADOW Scottish Secretary George Robertson yesterday called for a full
debate on the sale of the Scotsman newspaper group and its implications
for Scotland.
Departing from a prepared speech to the Scottish Arts Lobby (Salvo) in
Edinburgh, he said: ''I do not believe anybody in Scotland, whether they
are fans or otherwise of the Scotsman, can be anything other than
concerned at the fact that this newspaper group is up for auction in the
marketplace.
''There is a collective responsibility on all of us that it remains
editorially independent and does not become the plaything of a mogul in
the international media field.
''I would also hope that the diversity of the Scottish press which we
have become used to -- and some of us suffer from -- is maintained and
protected.''
</TEXT>
